We employ the following notation to describe the study design:
– i: one of the 22 strata (municipalities);
– Mi: number of primary sampling units (households) in the ith stratum, i = 1, …, 22;
– Si: number of primary sampling units (households) selected from the ith stratum, i = 1, …, 22;
– mi: number of primary sampling units (households) actually enrolled in the study from the ith stratum, i = 1, …, 22;
– Pi: number of individuals living within the ith stratum, i = 1, …, 22 (census data);
– pi: number of individuals actually enrolled in the study from the ith stratum, i = 1, …, 22;

